    <abstract>Kitajima Sinichi believes that all rock cut sutras were once colored, to match the
        coloring of the statues and niches. His first example for this is the Wenshushili suoshuo
        boreboluomi jing in cave 2 of Nan Xiangtangshan, where he did find pigments, and also cave 3
        of Bei Xiangtangshan, where he hasn’t found any pigments yet. He assumes the same for Mount
        Jian, because of Tang Yong’s connection to that place.</abstract>
